snippet.textDisplay: Seams we are back in the megapixel war in order to sell phones (looking at Sony circa. 2013). More pixels doesn't mean better pictures. More pixels on a small sensor means worse quality pixels, so you have to rely on better image processing. The quality of this processing is yet to be seen. Personally I think a bump from 16 to 24/30mp and better physical lens would have been the way to go. 100+mp on a sensor the size of a 5p means nothing. Its just specs on a piece of paper. Specs to hoodwink people to upgrade from a S10. Samsung needs to work on its image processing, has its still behind Google and Apple!
snippet.textOriginal: Seams we are back in the megapixel war in order to sell phones (looking at Sony circa. 2013). More pixels doesn't mean better pictures.
